Description: On offer is a superlative Eastman jazz/blues guitar, the AR605CE. This guitar is a wonderful balance between warm jazz and blues, yet harmoniously complex that is addictive..leaves finding other guitars almost 2 dimensional! A big boast I know, but it definitely is on par with much more expensive jazz guitars worth 1000's more! Comes out in a hard case and certificate of authenticity. The guitar is in good condition and has been checked out thorougly. No cracks, No bad fret issues, no structural problems. It has a little bit of finish (nitrocellulose) crazing in the nitro finish (which is common for this type of finish) but nothing you can see unless you hold it up to the light and look sideways, otherwise ready for gigging, or enjoying at home without any problems. Electronic, the Tone and Volume knobs (which are slider wheels under the pickguard) work perfectly and the Eastman/Kent Armstrong pickup is good enough to not have to replace.
